    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Transition Panels</title>
        <para>The bus body transition panels are located at the front corners of the bus body directly below the
            windshield side panels. The driver side transition panel (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f4700652">Fig. 52, Item 2</hotlnk>) is furnished with fresh air openings (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f4700652">Fig. 52, Item 3</hotlnk>) to the driver heater assembly.
        </para>
        <figure id="f4700652" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g4700652.png" type="png" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="288px"
                     scalefitheight="288px"/>
            <caption>Figure 52. Transition Panel- Driver Side Shown</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. OPTIONAL COWL MOUNTED AMBER DIRECTIONAL LIGHT</callout1>
                <callout1>2. DRIVER SIDE TRANSITION PANEL</callout1>
                <callout1>3. FRESH AIR INLET TO HEATER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>4. DRIVER SIDE FENDER EXTENSION</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcsubproc>
